---
title: Honey-Butter BBQ Pork Chops with Mashed Sweet Potatoes & Lemony Green Beans
description: The easiest way to add tons of restaurant-level flair to a dish with almost no effort? Two words: compound butter. For chefs, this ingredient is the ultimate secret weapon to making can’t-put-your-fork-down meals. Here, we’ve mixed softened butter with honey and salt. It’s dolloped onto warm, BBQ-spiced pork chops. The sweet, savory, slightly smoky combo is guaranteed to delight. Once you try a bite, don’t be surprised when you find yourself making excuses to whip it up again!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64107716417a213382064ccb-c2691259.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6492e6b63477e872b82f01a9.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 33 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 520 mg
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 25 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-butter-bbq-pork-chops-6492e6b63477e872b82f01a9
---

Wash and dry produce (except green beans). Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into
½-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by
2 inches. Cover, bring to a boil, and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return sweet potatoes to #pot{}. Add @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and @butter{0.5%tbsp}; mash until smooth using a #potato masher{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While sweet potatoes cook, place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{};
microwave until softened, ~{10-15%seconds}.

Stir in @honey{2%tsp} and a pinch of salt. This is your honey-butter compound
butter.

Pat @pork chops{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then rub all over with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.

While pork cooks, pierce @green beans{6%oz} bag with a fork; place bag on a
#plate{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam green beans in a small pot with a splash
> of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully transfer green beans to a #medium bowl{} and toss with lemon zest,
@butter{0.5%tbsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

Divide mashed sweet potatoes and green beans between plates. Top mashed sweet
potatoes with pork. Dollop pork with honey butter and sprinkle with
@?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired.

Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.